<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER PSO140-61 - DISASSEMBLE -
        INPUT GEAR
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="5">
        <title>INPUT GEAR</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The input gear and shaft are separate components secured with a snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301445">Figure 45</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301445" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301445" filename="../figg13/G1301445.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 45. Input Gear and Shaft Secured With snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301446">Figure 46</hotlnk>shows the input subassembly when disassembled.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301446" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301446" filename="../figg13/G1301446.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 46. Input Gear Subassembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The input bearing is a press fit into the input bearing cap (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301447">Figure 47</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301447" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301447" filename="../figg13/G1301447.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 47. Input Bearing is Press Fit into Input Bearing Cap</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the pocket bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301448">Figure 48</hotlnk>) with a suitable puller.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301448" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301448" filename="../figg13/G1301448.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 48. Remove Pocket Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The snap ring in the input shaft secures the gear in its proper location (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301449">Figure 49</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301449" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301449" filename="../figg13/G1301449.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 49. Snap Ring in Input Shaft Secures Gear in Proper Location</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
